main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a triangular object moving rapidly from north to south in Guadalupe, Arizona on October 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as chlorotic in shape and about the size of a nickel., The observation lasted for 15 minutes., The witnesses included two brothers and one sister., The weather at the time of the sighting was clear with a temperature of 65 degrees., The sighting was concluded to possibly be an aircraft or unusual atmospheric refraction.
witness description: family members including two brothers and one sister, with one being 17 years old.
